Masala curries are versatile tomato-based dishes that work with a variety of proteins and vegetables. Here, we're using a mix of cod, salmon and smoked haddock, perfect for soaking up the delicious flavour of the masala curry sauce.

== Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.
Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}, then pop it on top of the pan and allow to
steam until ready to serve.

== Fish ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain the @Fish Pie Mix{1%pack} and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Stir in the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Curry Powder Mix{1%sachet}, garlic and
@Tikka Masala Paste{75%g}. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{75%g}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g} and
@Water for the Sauce{150%ml}. Bring up to the boil.

Gently stir through the fish pie mix.

Lower the heat and simmer gently, stirring occasionally, until the fish is
cooked, ~{5-8%minutes}.

> The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

== Spinach and Finishing ==

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and
piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Butter{20%g} and @Honey{1%tbsp} into the curry until melted. Taste
and season with salt and @pepper{} if needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}.

Share your rice between bowls and top with the fish curry.

Sprinkle over the @Toasted Flaked Almonds{15%g} to finish.

Enjoy!